{
  "stem": "9262.6",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They didn't say, what size are you, anything like this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They just looked at you, gave you a bundle, which meant a shirt, a pair of trousers, a jacket, a coat, and a pair of shoes.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "No socks.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "No underwear, all right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when it was ill-fitting from the beginning, it would always be ill fitting, till the day they died.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they always said, it's far better to get something bigger because if you find something on the way, you can always stuff it in your trousers or you can wrap it around yourself.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So always take something bigger.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we got something big.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Who told you that?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some of the prisoners before they were dishing it out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were already dressed, and we came out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were told to stay in a different block.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They marched us out, and we went in the block.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So after two days, they came and took particulars-- our names, where we come from, our family.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And because these people who were doing the writing were put in charge by the Germans, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] they didn't understand the German which we were speaking, because they came from a different region.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So mistakes were made in the spelling of the name, in the birth.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Like say, for instance, if you say you were born on the 16th, they understood it was the 18th.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Or the 18th, they understood it was the 28th or something like this.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But it didn't really make any difference what they, what they wrote down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then we were tattooed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When we had the tattoo, we were already considered cannon fodder.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "This means that we had to work for the Germans, for the government.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
